---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="School Admissions Timeline England 2025–2026 | catchment.school"
  description="Key dates for primary and secondary school applications in England. When applications open, deadlines, National Offer Day dates, and appeal timelines."
>
  <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6 flex gap-2">
    <a href="/" class="hover:underline">Home</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <a href="/guides" class="hover:underline">Guides</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <span>School admissions timeline</span>
  </nav>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-10">
    <article class="lg:col-span-2 prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h1>School Admissions Timeline in England 2025–2026</h1>
      <p class="lead text-lg text-gray-600">
        Missing a key admissions date can push your application to the back of the queue. Here are all the
        critical dates for primary and secondary school applications in England.
      </p>

      <h2>Secondary school (Year 7) — 2025 entry</h2>
      <div class="not-prose">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-indigo-50">
              <th class="text-left p-3 border font-semibold">Date</th>
              <th class="text-left p-3 border font-semibold">Event</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {[
              ['May–June 2024', '11+ grammar school registration opens (where applicable)'],
              ['September–October 2024', '11+ tests take place'],
              ['1 September 2024', 'Secondary applications open'],
              ['31 October 2024', 'Application deadline (national closing date)'],
              ['1 March 2025', 'National Offer Day — Year 7 offers released'],
              ['15 March 2025', 'Deadline to accept or decline offer'],
              ['March–April 2025', 'Appeal deadline for refused places'],
              ['May–June 2025', 'Independent appeal hearings'],
            ].map(([date, event]) => (
              <tr class="border-b">
                <td class="p-3 border font-medium text-indigo-700 w-48">{date}</td>
                <td class="p-3 border">{event}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2>Primary school (Reception / Year R) — 2025 entry</h2>
      <div class="not-prose">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-indigo-50">
              <th class="text-left p-3 border font-semibold">Date</th>
              <th class="text-left p-3 border font-semibold">Event</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {[
              ['September 2024', 'Primary applications open'],
              ['15 January 2025', 'Application deadline (national closing date)'],
              ['16 April 2025', 'National Offer Day — Reception offers released'],
              ['30 April 2025', 'Deadline to accept or decline offer'],
              ['May 2025', 'Appeal deadline for refused places'],
              ['June–July 2025', 'Independent appeal hearings'],
            ].map(([date, event]) => (
              <tr class="border-b">
                <td class="p-3 border font-medium text-indigo-700 w-48">{date}</td>
                <td class="p-3 border">{event}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2>What happens if you apply late?</h2>
      <p>
        Late applications — those received after the national closing date — are processed only after all
        on-time applications have been considered. This means that even if you live very close to your
        preferred school, a late application may result in no place being available.
      </p>
      <p>
        Some local authorities do accept late applications with extenuating circumstances (e.g. recent
        move to the area, serious illness). Contact your local authority as soon as possible if you have
        missed the deadline.
      </p>

      <h2>In-year admissions</h2>
      <p>
        If you need a school place outside of the normal admissions round — for example because your family
        has moved to the area mid-year — you apply through the <strong>in-year admissions</strong> process.
        Contact your local authority admissions team, who will coordinate with schools to find an available place.
      </p>
    </article>

    <aside class="space-y-5">
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Key dates to remember</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li><strong>31 Oct</strong> — Secondary deadline</li>
          <li><strong>15 Jan</strong> — Primary deadline</li>
          <li><strong>1 Mar</strong> — Secondary offers</li>
          <li><strong>16 Apr</strong> — Primary offers</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-indigo-50 rounded-xl p-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Find schools near you</h3>
        <a href="/" class="block text-center bg-indigo-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-800 transition-colors">
          Search by postcode →
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="border rounded-xl p-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Related guides</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li><a href="/guides/how-school-catchment-areas-work" class="text-indigo-700 hover:underline">How catchment areas work</a></li>
          <li><a href="/guides/primary-school-catchment" class="text-indigo-700 hover:underline">Primary school catchment</a></li>
          <li><a href="/guides/secondary-school-catchment" class="text-indigo-700 hover:underline">Secondary school catchment</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>
</Base>
